{{Documentation subpage}}
<!-- PLEASE ADD CATEGORIES AT THE BOTTOM OF THIS PAGE -->
{{redirect|Template:Machine translation|the stub template|Template:Machine-translation-stub}}
{{Lua|Module:ISO 639 name}}
{{Twinkle standard installation}}
'''{{tl|{{PAGENAME}}}}'''  will categorise tagged articles into [[:Category:Wikipedia articles needing cleanup after translation]].

== Usage ==

{{tlc|Rough translation|language}}

== Parameters ==
There are three positional (unnamed) parameters, and two named parameters:

: {{para|1}} – name of language (required)
: {{para|2}} – name of language in "languages" list, if different (see example below); explicitly set to an empty value (<code>|2=|</code>) if the original is not an article on another language's Wikipedia, or is absent from the list of languages displayed (optional) 
: {{para|3}} – replaces the word "article"; e.g. use "section" for use in a section. {{tl|Rough translation-section}} implies this. (optional) 
: {{para|listed}} –  set to "yes" if the article has been listed at [[Wikipedia:Pages needing translation into English]] (optional)
: {{para|date}} – month and year; if omitted, a bot will supply it later. (optional)

== Example ==
:{{tlc|Rough translation|German|Deutsch|section}}
Alternative version of this
:{{tlc|Rough translation|1{{=}}German|2{{=}}Deutsch|3{{=}}section}}

If the second parameter is filled in as in the example above, the template will display
:<code>The original article is under "Deutsch" in the languages list.</code>
Otherwise, the message displayed is a generic
:<code>The original article is available in the languages list.</code>
However, if argument 2 is explicitly set to empty (<code>|2=|</code>), then neither message appears. This is the format to use when the original is not an article on another language's Wikipedia, or it isn't listed in the languages list.

This template will categorize tagged articles into [[:Category:Wikipedia articles needing cleanup after translation]].
It should not be [[Wikipedia:Subst|substituted]].

== TemplateData ==
{{TemplateData header}}
<templatedata>
{
    "description": "Use this template to indicate that an article or section is a rough translation from another language and may have been generated by a computer or by a translator without dual proficiency.",
	"format": "inline",
	"params": {
		"1": {
			"label": "Language",
			"description": "The language the article or section is a rough translation from",
			"type": "line",
			"example": "French",
			"required": true
		},
		"listed": {
			"label": "Listed on WP:PNT?",
			"description": "Enter \"y\", \"yes\", \"true\", \"on\" or \"1\" here if this article is listed on \"Wikipedia:Pages needing translation into English\" to add a link to its entry.",
			"type": "line",
			"autovalue": "y",
			"example": "y"
		},
		"2": {
			"label": "Alternative native name of language",
			"description": "Custom text to replace the language's indicated native name as it appears in the \"Languages\" list",
			"type": "line"
		},
		"3": {
			"label": "Affected area",
			"description": "Text to replace the word \"article\", usually \"section\"",
			"type": "string",
			"autovalue": "section",
			"example": "section"
		},
		"date": {
			"label": "Month and year",
			"description": "The month and year that the template was placed (in full). \"May 2025\" inserts the current month and year automatically.",
			"type": "line",
			"autovalue": "May 2025",
			"example": "January 2013",
			"suggested": true
		}
	},
	"paramOrder": [
		"1",
        "listed",
		"2",
        "3",
		"date"
	]
}
</templatedata>

== See also ==
* [[Wikipedia:Template messages/Translation]]
* {{tl|Translated page}} &ndash; for use on Talk page
* {{tl|Expand language}}
* {{tl|Google translation}}
* {{tl|Hidden translation}}
* {{tl|Machine translate}}
* {{tl|Not English}}
* {{tl|Proofreader needed}}
* {{tl|Whose translation}}

